{
  "stem": "11744.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There will never be a war and we've got-- Hitler and I dealt together, and we are avoiding a war for the rest of the century.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And eight months later, August 1939, the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So these were my first five years of married life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Then the next five years it was war-- so my husband was fighting and fighting in the French resistance and--",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Terrible.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was very, very bad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, everybody was saying there's not-- no time to get children, you shouldn't have children in a time like this.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We still all said we want children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How much do we wait, and when do we do?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We're waiting.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I had my daughter who was born in '35, and my second daughter was born in '39-- three months, four months before the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And from that time on, of course, our life was completely-- disintegrated completely.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was at that-- at a seashore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My husband was mobilized.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was with his-- with his army corps, and went into the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, he went on the Maginot Line like-- like most of them did.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this line was built in order to stop the German from ever invading France, but they turned around.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They didn't have-- they didn't have to go through it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They turned around and went into Belgium way up in the frontier, on the northern frontier and invade France from the north instead of doing it from the east.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Why he was taken prisoner?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I said he was taken prisoner--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, and without my knowledge, because in being a Red Cross nurse I was entitled certain details of what was going on that maybe just the-- the private people didn't get.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
